HEADWORD: Suint
<hw>Su"int</hw> <pr>(s⟦umac⟧"⟦icr⟧nt)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A peculiar substance obtained
from the wool of sheep, consisting largely of potash mixed with fatty
and earthy matters. It is used as a source of potash and also for the
manufacture of gas.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

